An international summit hosted by Indonesia will address the earthquake and tsunami aftermath, with 23 countries and major organizations participating.
Japan has deployed troops to aid in rescue efforts, focusing on Indonesia.
Uzbekistan and China have sent humanitarian aid, while Australia pledges 1 billion Australian dollars in assistance.
The death toll in Indonesia surpasses 95,000, with nearly 500,000 homeless.
Japan commits to long-term reconstruction projects, and Bangladesh sends relief goods to tsunami victims.
The global response underscores solidarity in the face of this devastating natural disaster.
